    "description": {
      "gm": "",
      "value": "<p id=\"docs-internal-guid-7ef03dda-7fff-1833-8e31-fda79cb44bbf\" dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;text-indent:9pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:bold;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Prerequisites </span><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">short leg, expert in Religion, worships Lashtada</span></p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.2;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Sobbing piteously in a prone condition over a deceased creature for ten minutes, your cries reach the ears of your matron, replicating the effects of the </span><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:italic;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">resurrect</span><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\"> ritual with a level equal to half your own without the need for any casters but yourself.Â </span></p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.2;text-indent:9pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">The gold cost in diamonds need not be paid in diamonds. Lashtada prefers items with emotional value, but the gold cost remains. This price may be paid in the future, but must be paid before this ability can be used again, or risk her wrath. If a short leg choses, without coercion, magical or otherwise, they may offer themselves as the cost, immediately dying if the target is revived, but with all debts to Lashtada forgiven.</span></p>"
